CHRISTCHURCH - New Zealand defeated South Africa by six runs in the second one-day international in Christchurch on Wednesday to level the five-match series at 1-1.The Black Caps set the Proteas a target of 290 -- after losing the toss and being sent into bat -- aided by an unbeaten 102 from Ross Taylor.The tourists fell just short, making nine for 283 in reply, with Dwaine Pretorius's 26-ball half century a highlight.Ross Taylor's record-breaking century proves to be just enough as New Zealand level the series to win the 2nd #NZvSA ODI by 6 runs pic.twitter.com/jW1uX9zEscAFP